KEY PRODUCT FEATURES:
• 2 ready-to-play 60-card Magic decks (basic lands included)
• 1 traditional foil card in each deck
• 1 Play Guide booklet + 2 deck storage boxes
• 1 MTG Arena Code Card to unlock both decks for two people to play online at MTG Arena
• Game night for two—grab a friend and learn how to play Magic: The Gathering!

DESCRIPTION:
The 2021 Arena Starter Kit contains 2 ready-to-play 60 card decks—with 1 traditional foil Rare card and 4 nonfoil Rare cards, 2 deck storage boxes, 1 Rules and World-of-Magic booklet, and 1 twice-redeemable MTG Arena Code Card for two people to unlock both decks online at MTG Arena. Both decks include basic lands and feature cards from Magic: The Gathering’s Dungeons & Dragons, mage school, and Viking-themed sets—Adventures in the Forgotten Realms, Strixhaven: School of Mages, and Kaldheim.

KEY PRODUCT FEATURES:
• 10 Adventures in the Forgotten Realms (AFR) Magic: The Gathering Draft Boosters
• 1 foil alt-art promo card—Treasure Chest
• 3 oversized dungeon cards
• 40 basic land cards (20 foil + 20 nonfoil)
• Oversized d20 and MTG card storage box
• Beloved Dungeons & Dragons heroes and monsters have ventured into Magic for the ultimate crossover!

DESCRIPTION:
The Adventures in the Forgotten Realms Bundle contains 10 Adventures in the Forgotten Realms Draft Boosters, 1 traditional foil alt-art promo card—Treasure Chest, 3 oversized dungeon cards (Tomb of Annihilation, Dungeon of the Mad Mage, and Lost Mine of Phandelver), 40 basic lands (20 traditional foils and 20 nonfoils), 1 oversized d20, 1 card storage box, and 2 reference cards.

Each Adventures in the Forgotten Realms Draft Booster contains 15 Magic cards and a token or ad card, with 1 Rare or Mythic Rare, 3 Uncommons, 10 Common cards, and 1 Land card. A traditional foil card of any rarity replaces a Common in 33% of Adventures in the Forgotten Realms Draft Boosters. Traditional foil Mythic Borderless Planeswalker in less than 1% of boosters.

DESCRIPTION:
The Adventures in the Forgotten Realms Set Booster Box contains 30 Adventures in the Forgotten Realms Set Boosters. Each Set Booster contains 12 Magic cards, 1 Art Card (includes a D&D monster stat block on the back in 33% of packs), and 1 token, ad card, or special card from Magic's history (a card from "The List"). Each pack contains a combination of 1–4 Rares or Mythic Rares, 7–10 Uncommons and Commons (maximum of 7 may be Uncommon), and 1 Land card. One non–Art Card and non–Land card of any rarity is a traditional foil. A foil-stamped Signature Art Card replaces the Art Card in 5% of Set Boosters. A card from The List replaces the token or ad card in 25% of Set Boosters.
